      • getCombinations

        private static java.util.ArrayList<java.util.ArrayList<Player>> getCombinations(java.util.ArrayList<Player> a,
                                                                                int prev,
                                                                                int depth)
        Through some miracle this function actually works. It takes a list and as long as the number of elements of it is even, it returns every combination of half the elements in efficiently and recursively. ex. Input = [1, 2, 3, 4] Output = [[1,2],[1,3],[1,4],[2,3],[2,4],[3,4]]
        Parameters:
        a - The list
        prev - Set to -1
        depth - Set to 0
        Returns:
        A list of every of every combination of the input.
